      "review_summary": "The PR detects BlueBubbles cron delivery mirrors in Codex history and prepends a continuity guard assembled from recent cron messages and global/project memory files to the next non-cron turn.\n\nPR surface: Source +200, Tests +17. Total +217 across 3 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. for the introduced defect: run a non-default agent or bound project with distinct default-workspace memory and trigger the restore branch; the source deterministically includes the default workspace. The original continuity failure itself still lacks direct before/after live evidence.",
